# Dockerfile for the ASDN Net-Tools Image
# ==========================================
# This image will be used throughout the course as a "network workstation"
# for testing, debugging, and exploring container networking.
#
# Requirements:
#   1. Use ubuntu:22.04 as the base image
#   2. Install networking tools (see list below)
#   3. Set bash as the default shell
#
# Tools to install:
#   - iproute2        (ip command)
#   - iputils-ping    (ping command)
#   - traceroute      (traceroute command)
#   - tcpdump         (packet capture)
#   - curl            (HTTP client)
#   - wget            (file downloader)
#   - dnsutils        (dig, nslookup)
#   - netcat-openbsd  (nc command)
#   - iptables        (firewall)
#   - net-tools       (ifconfig, netstat)
#   - nmap            (network scanner)
#   - vim             (text editor)
#
# Best practices:
#   - Combine RUN commands to reduce layers
#   - Clean up apt cache to reduce image size
#   - Use DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive

